[Question]
What is the difference between `print` and `printf`?

public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, world!");
    }
}
```

[Answer]
The main difference between `print` and `printf` is that `printf` supports formatting characters such as `%d` or `%f`. These formatting characters help you insert various data types like integers or floating point numbers into strings. On the other hand, `print` simply prints out strings without any additional formatting options. In this case, both `print` and `printf` would produce the same output.

