If you want to convert a program from one language to another, you'll need to do two things:
\begin{itemize}
\item Understand what the program does.
\item Translate the program in such a way that it can be written in the target language.
\end{itemize}

For the first part, if this is your own code, try running it yourself. If it's someone else's code, use a debugger to see what each line does, or read the comments and understand what variables mean, etc. For a small piece of code like this, you should be able to get away without much effort.

Once you understand the code, look at the syntax of both languages.

