The question is simple to understand, but I'll explain it again anyway. Write a code that outputs `Hello World` when executed as a Java program. It has to be written in Java, and it has to be able to run.

To write this, we need to know what a Java program looks like. Fortunately, there are plenty of resources on the internet that teach you how to write your first Java program. [Here](https://www.w3schools.com/java/default.asp) is one such resource.

